  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Grant Aid for People Affected by the Military Engagement in Tigray Region, Ethiopia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The conflict in Tigray region of Ethiopia, coupled with pre-existing humanitarian needs and the COVID-19 pandemic context in northern Ethiopia, has created a concerning, volatile humanitarian situation, as numerous civilians have been displaced within Tigray, into other Ethiopian Regional States, and into neighbouring states of Sudan. The project aims to contribute to the improvement of the physical and mental wellbeing, as well as living conditions for crisis-affected populations in Northern Ethiopia through the provision of essential health and mental health and psychosocial support, as well as shelter repair assistance. The intervention targets internally displaced persons (IDPs), host communities, and returnee IDPs affected by the Northern Ethiopian Crisis in Tigray and Amhara regions.</narrative>
  </description>
